# Markdown

Markdown is a file-based product management tool that does NOT use MCP. Instead, [features], [stories], and [tasks] are stored as markdown files in `.workspace/task-manager/`, simulating the same structure as tools like Jira, Azure DevOps, and Linear using local files.

## Terminology Mapping

| Generic Term | Markdown |
|---|---|
| `[Feature]` | Feature markdown file |
| `[Story]` | Story markdown file |
| `[Task]` | Task header (## 1 Title) |
| `[Checklist]` | Checkbox bullet (- [ ]) |

## Status Mapping

| Generic Status | Markdown |
|---|---|
| `[Planned]` | [Planned] |
| `[Active]` | [Active] |
| `[Review]` | [Review] |
| `[Completed]` | [Completed] |

## ID Mapping

| Generic ID | Markdown |
|---|---|
| `featureId` | File path to prd.mdc |
| `storyId` | File path to story.mdc |
| `taskId` | Task number (1, 2, 3) |

## Initialization

If `.workspace/task-manager` does not exist, run: `dotnet run --project developer-cli -- init-task-manager`, which will create a nested .git repository, so these files are not tracked by the parent repository.

## File Structure

```
.workspace/task-manager/
  └─ yyyy-MM-dd-[feature-title]/
      ├─ prd.mdc (feature description)
      ├─ 1-[story-title].mdc (first story with tasks)
      ├─ 2-[story-title].mdc (second story with tasks)
      └─ ...
```

## Task format in story files

```markdown
# Story Title

**Purpose:** What this story delivers
**NOT included:** Out of scope items
**Dependencies:** Prerequisites
**IMPORTANT:** Scope warning

## 1 Task title [Planned]
- [ ] Checklist item 1
- [ ] Checklist item 2

## 2 Another task title [Planned]
- [ ] Checklist item
```

## Task Identification

- [Task] identifiers are numeric (1, 2, 3, ...)
- [Task] numbers are sequential within each [story] file
- [Task] headers include numbers: `## 1 Task title [Status]`

## Critical Rules

- storyId is a file path (e.g., ".workspace/task-manager/2025-10-25-feature-title/1-backend.md")
- taskId is a task number (e.g., "1", "2", "3")
- Update status by editing markdown file headers
